Insider Activity


Individual




James S. Metcalf



Mr. James S. Metcalf is Independent Outside Director at Tenneco, Inc., Chairman, President & Chief Executive Officer at USG Corp., a Member at Union League Club, a Member at The Executives Club of Chicago, and a Member at Chicago Cares, Inc. He is on the Board of Directors at Tenneco, Inc., CGC, Inc., INROADS Chicago, The Robert Crown Center for Health Education, University System of Georgia Foundation, Inc., National Association of Manufacturers, and The USG Foundation.
Mr. Metcalf was previously employed as Independent Director by Molex, Inc., President & Chief Executive Officer by L&W Supply Corp., National Accounts Manager by United States Gypsum Co., President by USG Building Systems, and Senior Vice President-Sales & Marketing by USG Interiors, Inc.
He received his undergraduate degree from The Ohio State University and an MBA from Pepperdine University.



